## skill-reflect (session quality nudge)

At the end of any session that used distributed skills (plugin, marketplace, or
repo-sourced), you may offer a privacy-safe quality review — only if there was
noticeable friction (unexpected errors, stale guidance, repeated workarounds):

> "This session used distributed skills. Want me to run `skill-reflect` to capture
> feedback for the skill author(s)? It creates a local Markdown file — nothing is
> sent anywhere without your explicit approval."

Rules: offer only; never run automatically; `skill-reflect` requires a second,
explicit consent step before anything leaves the machine.
